Sentencas: A cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-delta (BSFNb) perovskite-type oxide was investigated as the cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells (IT-SOFCs) with Sm0.2Ce0.8O1.9 (SDC) electrolyte.
Titulo: Evaluation of a cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: XRD results showed that BSFNb cathode was chemically compatible with the electrolyte SDC up to 1,000 A degrees C.
Titulo: Evaluation of a cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The maximum output of anode-supported thin-film SOFC reached 503 mW cm(-2) at 650 A degrees C when employing humidified H-2 as fuel and static air as oxidizer.
Titulo: Evaluation of a cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The electrode polarization resistance was low as 0.078 Omega cm(2) at 650 A degrees C, and the activation energy of the electrode polarization resistance was 129.72 kJ mol(-1).
Titulo: Evaluation of a cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells

Sentencas: The experimental results indicated that the cobalt-free BSFNb was a promising cathode candidate for IT-SOFCs.
Titulo: Evaluation of a cobalt-free Ba0.5Sr0.5Fe0.9Nb0.1O3-δ cathode material for intermediate-temperature solid oxide fuel cells
